CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 6, 1941, pg. 8 reads: "To Model For Sweet Charity's Sake - Above, a few of the beauties that will model in fashion and hair style show Monday night, December 8, at Wesley Centre AME Zion Church. Proceeds will benefit needy families at Xmas time, and the Coleman Home.  Reading from left to right, Miss Anna Bush, Miss Beatrice Wilburn, Miss Beatrice Tucker, (director and manager of style show), Mrs. Noraella Stokes, and Miss Geraldine Richardson."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Anna Bush, Beatrice Wilburn, Beatrice Tucker, Noraella Stokes, and Geraldine Richardson, posed in Harris studio
